Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on natural language grounding and language interpretation in the context of visual scenes, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with visual scenes and navigation, which is a core area of computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with developing agents that can interpret natural language instructions and navigate in dynamic environments, which is a core area of AI research. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a discriminator model to evaluate the quality of augmented data, which is a machine learning technique. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with navigation in dynamic environments, which is a core area of robotics research.
